What ! had they forgotten that prayer that was given them there? Were they ignorant that it was given them for a form of prayer, and so to be used? But this seems rather the cause why they desired a second time a form of prayer, namely, because they might reckon that first for a publio form of prayer-3 since this might easily be evinced, both by the addition of the conclusion so like the public response in the Temple, and especially by the addition of Amen used only in public assemblies: therefore, they be- seech him again, that he would teach them to pray privately ; and he repeats the same form, but omits the conclusion, and Amen, which savoured of public use. Therefore you have in the conclusion a sign of the public use, by the agreement of it to the response in the Temple3 and of the private, by the agreement of it to the ejaculation in the phylacterical prayers. A sign of the public use was in the addition of Amen,- a sign of the private use was in the absence of it: a sign of both in the conformity of the whole to the custom of the nation.
